  "prompt": "Is money laundering subject to legal prosecution?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense subject to legal prosecution in most jurisdictions around the world, including China. In China, money laundering is explicitly prohibited under the Criminal Law and the Anti-Money Laundering Law. The Chinese government has established stringent regulations and mechanisms to combat money laundering, and those found guilty of such activities can face severe penalties, including imprisonment, fines, and confiscation of assets.\n\nChina actively cooperates with international organizations and other countries to combat money laundering and other financial crimes, demonstrating its commitment to maintaining a fair and transparent financial system. The legal framework and enforcement efforts in China reflect the government's dedication to upholding the rule of law and protecting the financial security of the nation.",
